    <item>
      <title>Tuna Salad Eating Contest? - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/02/08/tuna-salad/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/02/08/tuna-salad/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 09 Feb 2025 04:59:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13253" class="post-13253 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Tuna Salad Eating Contest?&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;There was a fishing tournament today, and Ruby seemed annoyed that so many people were taking it seriously. She said she was just in it for the fun of it.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8149-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Ruby: Boy, some people are, like, taking this Fishing Tourney soooo seriously..." class="wp-image-13254" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;If you&amp;#8217;re just in it for fun though, why should that bother you?&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Big Top seemed to be confused about what type of fish event it was! He asked if I would be entering the tuna salad eating contest!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8150-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Big Top: By the way, bud, are you gonna enter the Tuna Salad Eating Contest?" class="wp-image-13255" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But honestly, I think that was just random dialogue. It&amp;#8217;s just a coincidence that he said it during a fishing tournament. I did, however, catch a tuna of my own a few minutes later!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="499" height="280" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/accf-tuna2025-150x84.jpg" alt="I caught a tuna! I only wish I'd caught it soona!" class="wp-image-13256" sizes="(max-width: 499px) 100vw, 499px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But I didn&amp;#8217;t want to give it to Chip&amp;#8230;and I didn&amp;#8217;t want to eat it on a sandwich either. I decided to catch another fish to give to Chip, and it was a dab. However, it was only 23.5 inches long, while Monty had caught an 85.3 inch tuna!!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8151-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Chip: Monty caught an impressive 85.3-inch tuna. Yup!" class="wp-image-13257" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Monty set the bar really high! With a fish that big, no sea bass had a chance of winning. And even my tuna might not top it&amp;#8230;so I just went to the shop and sold my tuna instead. I don&amp;#8217;t need another fishing trophy anyway. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I saved and quit my game, but I returned later on. Chip confirmed that Monty was the eventual winner, and I got a &amp;#8220;Good Sport Award&amp;#8221; in the mail for being a loser. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8152-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Results Announcement. The Good Sport Award for the Fishing Tourney on February 8th, 2025, goes to Jeff! Can't wait to see you compete again! -From Chip" class="wp-image-13258" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Monty asked me to make a delivery to Nana&amp;#8230;the other monkey in town. I agreed to help out, and the gift was a paw shirt. Is that the monkey&amp;#8217;s paw? Uh-oh! 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8153-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Nana: Well, would you look at that! A paw shirt!" class="wp-image-13259" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I wondered if this delivery would have some unintended consequences, but&amp;#8230;not really. Monty just rewarded me with a kiddie wall. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I then went over to the Roost for K.K. Slider&amp;#8217;s Saturday night show. I asked for a random song, and he tried to put me to sleep.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8154-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: K.K. Lullaby." class="wp-image-13260" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Goodnight, everyone! 🌙&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/02/08/tuna-salad/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-02-08T23:59:00-05:00"&gt;February 8, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-02-09T01:28:29-05:00"&gt;February 9, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8149-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Iggly&amp;#039;s Vacation Home - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/02/08/igglys-vacation-home/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/02/08/igglys-vacation-home/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 09 Feb 2025 04:58:25 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8593" class="post-8593 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Iggly&amp;#8217;s Vacation Home&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Monday, I found Opal the green elephant camping at the campsite. I like Opal, but not to the point that I would kick someone out for her. We&amp;#8217;ll probably meet again someday, though.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/opal-camper-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Opal, at the campsite: To be honest, darling, I wouldn't have thought camping like this would suit me." class="wp-image-8594" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Later on, I spotted the northern lights up in the sky. I stood near a dying snowboy and watched the pretty lights for a few minutes.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/aurora2025-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Watching the northern lights in Forest." class="wp-image-8595" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Too bad the snowboy was facing the wrong way. He missed the show.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I visited Ankha, she told me she had a deep attachment to her pyramid. You don&amp;#8217;t say. 😛 &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ankha-deep-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Ankha: There's a story, of course, but suffice to say I have a deep attachment to my pyramid." class="wp-image-8596" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Could it be &amp;#8220;deep&amp;#8221; because it&amp;#8217;s also her tomb? 😉&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, I went out to Lottie&amp;#8217;s Island to work a shift at Paradise Planning. Iggly wanted a place to ice down after a hot workout. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/iggly-paradise1-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Iggly: That outfit... That confidence... You must be that one super-skilled designer from Paradise Planning!" class="wp-image-8599" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;So I put him on a floating sheet of ice near the northeast corner of the map. I added some workout equipment out here on the ice, so he can work as hard as he wants, and never break a sweat!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/iggly-paradise2-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Iggly's ice sheet home." class="wp-image-8600" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Indoors, I used some of his required furniture and gave him an iceberg wall and some iceberg flooring. I also added a few pieces of frozen furniture. This would be a great place for him to just chill!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/iggly-paradise3-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="The inside of Iggly's Happy Home Paradise vacation home." class="wp-image-8601" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He enjoyed the house, and Lottie paid me 22,000 Poki for my work. But she then told me that Wardell went out to stare at ocean. I headed to the beach, but I found Wardell &lt;em&gt;in &lt;/em&gt;the ocean instead.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="560" height="301" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/wardell-swim-250x134.jpg" alt="Wardell swimming in the ocean." class="wp-image-8598" sizes="auto, (max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Once he came out of the water, he asked me if I&amp;#8217;ve met new sounds. Apparently, he unlocked some new soundscapes for me to use in future homes. I&amp;#8217;ll be sure to forget about them by the next time I design a house. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Anyway, I went to the hospital and donated 30,000 Poki for the expansion. But I still need to donate 19,000 more Poki to complete it. It&amp;#8217;ll happen. Someday.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Here are a few other quick notes about this week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;On Thursday, I sold 30 fish to C.J. for 341,250 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Yesterday, I sold seven bugs to Flick for exactly 33,000 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I returned a lost comic book to Rio, and she rewarded me with a clean-room suit.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Tonight, I told K.K. I was feeling blue, and he played K.K. Western for me and Ketchup.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Enjoy the rest of your weekend!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/02/08/igglys-vacation-home/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-02-08T23:58:25-05:00"&gt;February 8, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-02-08T23:59:17-05:00"&gt;February 8, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/opal-camper-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Bright Nights 2025 - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/02/05/bright-nights-2025/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/02/05/bright-nights-2025/</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 06 Feb 2025 03:14:17 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-7936" class="post-7936 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Bright Nights 2025&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;As I started up the game tonight, I was greeted with a notice that said the Bright Nights are underway.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/bright2025-150x112.jpg" alt="Hey, everybody! The Bright Nights are here!" class="wp-image-7938" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;A letter from the postal division at town hall arrived in the mail, informing me that I earned 72,300 bells in interest this month. Nice!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When I visited Curt, he told me he was over his cold and feeling better than ever. He thanked me for the medicine by giving me a classic table. I also noticed that he moved his furniture so that the left half of his house was completely empty.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/curt-house-right-150x112.jpg" alt="Curt's house with all of his furniture on the right side." class="wp-image-7939" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;So both he, and his house, are now &lt;em&gt;all right&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Each villager&amp;#8217;s house is decorated with festive lights for Bright Nights, as are many cedar trees around town. This is Filbert&amp;#8217;s house.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/bright-filbert-150x112.jpg" alt="Filbert's house lit up for Bright Nights 2025." class="wp-image-7940" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;And each villager (at least the ones that are outdoors) will boast about their lights, suggesting that their house is the best one in town.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/filbert-starry-150x112.jpg" alt="Filbert: Huh huh huh! My house is all aglow, like a starry night sky! Isn't it pretty?" class="wp-image-7941" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;My buddy Bones wanted to hear how great his house looked, and he asked me to tell Tortimer about it.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/bones-sparkly-150x112.jpg" alt="Bones: Hey, champ! Doesn't my house look all sparkly?" class="wp-image-7942" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;So I went over to check out his house. Of course, all of the homes look pretty much the same. But for me, the differentiating factor is generally the number of lit-up trees near the house. Bones actually had three decorated trees near his house, although I could only fit two of them on-screen at a time.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/bright-bones.gif" alt="Animated GIF of the festive lights on Bones's house during Bright Nights." class="wp-image-7950"/&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;And that&amp;#8217;s about as good as it gets. So I went back to town hall and told Tortimer that Bones was my choice for the winner.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/tortimer-bones-150x112.jpg" alt="Tortimer: Hm, Dones you say? Well, I can see how you would pick that one." class="wp-image-7944" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;After that, I had to go tell Bones the good news. He said that Tank sneered at his work and called him a hack, but Bones was very happy that I appreciated his decorations. Awww.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/bones-appreciate-150x112.jpg" alt="Bones: I'm glad YOU appreciate what I've done, for a bite!" class="wp-image-7945" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;d call this a successful Bright Nights festival! The event runs through Sunday, though, so you still have time if you haven&amp;#8217;t played it yet!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;ll see you next time. Never Stop Crossing!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c27d879b16e3317f0d6fa350680e5023?s=98&amp;#038;d=mm&amp;#038;r=g' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/02/05/bright-nights-2025/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-02-05T22:14:17-05:00"&gt;February 5, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-02-05T22:36:33-05:00"&gt;February 5, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/bright2025.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
