    <item>
      <title>Marina Returns - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/02/01/marina-returns/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/02/01/marina-returns/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 02 Feb 2025 04:28:56 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13240" class="post-13240 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Marina Returns&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Today, I found a house in the same spot where Roscoe lived (until last week). When I went inside, I was very pleased to find Marina the octopus! 🐙&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8144-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Marina: Well, it's nice to meet you. I'm new here, so I'm sorry if I seem a little frazzles. My name is Marina." class="wp-image-13243" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;ve always liked Marina. She has lived here before, of course. In fact, she moved into Forest in &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2016/02/14/valentines-day-2016/"&gt;February of 2016&lt;/a&gt; as well! Welcome back, Marina!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I ran into Big Top over by Able Sisters, and he said that the first of every month is going to be Hide-and-Seek Day!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8145-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Big Top: You know what I just decided? The 1st of every month is gonna be Hide-and-Seek Day!" class="wp-image-13244" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Of course, he&amp;#8217;s not going to stick to that schedule. But we did play today! He gave me ten minutes to find him, Punchy, and Ruby&amp;#8230;and I found Ruby almost immediately. She was behind a coconut tree, between Marina&amp;#8217;s new house and Scott&amp;#8217;s house.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8146-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Ruby: Oh wow! You totally found me!" class="wp-image-13245" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Three minutes later, I found Punchy behind a tree on the cliff, south of Able Sisters.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="280" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/accf-punchy-rat-sm-150x84.jpg" alt="Punchy: Not to be a rat, but you have one of us left to find. So, hurry up and get to it." class="wp-image-13246" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;And with four minutes remaining on the timer, I found Big Top near the museum. He gave me a mini alloid for winning the game, and he complimented me on my X-ray vision. 🩻&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8147-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Big Top: We're no match for you and your X-ray vision, bud!" class="wp-image-13247" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Right afterwards, I spoke with Ruby and she complained about the lack of events lately. She said it was &amp;#8220;SOOOOO boring.&amp;#8221; It was as if she didn&amp;#8217;t know she just played a game of hide-and-seek. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Later on, I played again to attend K.K. Slider&amp;#8217;s Saturday night show. He performed one of my favorites for me: &amp;#8220;Two Days Ago.&amp;#8221; 👍&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8148-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: Two Days Ago." class="wp-image-13248" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I posted my latest ACCF video yesterday; check out City Folk Moments #24:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="ACCF - City Folk Moments #24 (Animal Crossing)" width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/w4YFsfO-wsg?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And last but not least, here are a few other quick notes about today&amp;#8217;s session:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;I shot down a balloon present that contained a brick block. &lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Felicity was sick with a cold, so I gave her some medicine.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I obtained four gyroids today (including the one from Big Top), but none were ones that I needed for Brewster.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;My buddy Butch was in the city, so I had a little chat with him. 🙂&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/02/01/marina-returns/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-02-01T23:28:56-05:00"&gt;February 1, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-02-01T23:30:29-05:00"&gt;February 1, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8144-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
